{"questionId":"30727443","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a semicircle with centre&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math>&nbsp;and radius&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>. Points&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P,&nbsp;Q</mtext></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>R</mtext></math>&nbsp;lie on the circumference of the circle, such that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>PQ</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>R</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>Q</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi>θ</mi></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b8aac0856ae90d12dcc7f2ded313b0f9e8026b2d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89549</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>90</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> if there is more than one solution. Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> for an answer&nbsp;in degrees.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"30727443","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.5b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence determine the value of θ.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNum